1
00:00:01,353 --> 00:00:08,583
♪

2
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:14,543
♪ (singing in Japanese) ♪

3
00:00:14,543 --> 00:01:45,403
♪

4
00:01:48,099 --> 00:01:50,119
What do you mean?

5
00:01:50,119 --> 00:01:52,979
You've gotta be lying
about Han'nya being dead.

6
00:01:52,979 --> 00:01:54,989
I swear I'm telling the truth.

7
00:01:54,989 --> 00:01:57,089
Four members of the
Oni Gang were killed.

8
00:01:57,089 --> 00:01:58,969
They were all trying
to protect Aoshi

9
00:01:58,969 --> 00:02:00,929
when they were machine
gunned to death.

10
00:02:00,929 --> 00:02:02,139
I can see Beshimi
dying in a fight,

11
00:02:02,139 --> 00:02:03,979
but no one could kill Han'nya.

12
00:02:03,979 --> 00:02:04,909
I was there,

13
00:02:04,909 --> 00:02:05,999
they were great fighters,

14
00:02:05,999 --> 00:02:07,959
but even they couldn't
outrun a gatling gun.

15
00:02:07,959 --> 00:02:09,169
They all died.

16
00:02:09,169 --> 00:02:10,179
What a waste of four men

17
00:02:10,179 --> 00:02:12,909
with such abilities.

18
00:02:12,909 --> 00:02:17,899
As a samurai son I give
you my word it's true.

19
00:02:17,899 --> 00:02:19,109
Because of that
terrible massacre

20
00:02:19,109 --> 00:02:21,129
Aoshi now wants to
avenge your friend's death

21
00:02:21,129 --> 00:02:23,929
by killing Kenshin Himura.

22
00:02:23,929 --> 00:02:25,929
He thinks killing Kenshin
will prove to everyone

23
00:02:25,929 --> 00:02:27,159
how powerful the Oni Gang is,

24
00:02:27,159 --> 00:02:30,029
even though Kenshin had
nothing to do with their demise.

25
00:02:30,029 --> 00:02:32,079
I can't believe
Aoshi would do that.

26
00:02:32,079 --> 00:02:34,929
And that so many of my
dear friends are gone.

27
00:02:34,929 --> 00:02:38,159
♪

28
00:02:42,949 --> 00:02:51,969
♪

29
00:02:51,969 --> 00:02:53,049
You are the first outsider

30
00:02:53,049 --> 00:02:55,079
that's ever been
allowed to visit us here,

31
00:02:55,079 --> 00:02:58,089
and we welcome you, Aoshi.

32
00:02:58,089 --> 00:03:01,059
Now tell us what has
prompted your visit.

33
00:03:01,059 --> 00:03:02,979
I wanted to talk
with you, Shishio.

34
00:03:02,979 --> 00:03:04,119
To get some information.

35
00:03:04,119 --> 00:03:05,909
But let me make
it perfectly clear,

36
00:03:05,909 --> 00:03:08,189
I'm not here to join
your little group.

37
00:03:08,189 --> 00:03:09,929
I see.

38
00:03:09,929 --> 00:03:10,939
Well, I'm disappointed,

39
00:03:10,939 --> 00:03:14,079
but I'll help if I can.

40
00:03:14,079 --> 00:03:15,169
You're obviously skilled enough

41
00:03:15,169 --> 00:03:17,159
to be part of my organization,

42
00:03:17,159 --> 00:03:18,989
but as much as I admire you

43
00:03:18,989 --> 00:03:21,029
I sense you like
to be your own boss,

44
00:03:21,029 --> 00:03:23,949
and I'm the only
boss around here.

45
00:03:23,949 --> 00:03:26,129
Now, is this about Battosai?

46
00:03:26,129 --> 00:03:28,169
Because if it is I do
have information about him

47
00:03:28,169 --> 00:03:29,969
that's very valuable.

48
00:03:29,969 --> 00:03:31,999
Before you tell me anything
I want you to understand

49
00:03:31,999 --> 00:03:34,149
I'm not offering to
kill Battosai for you.

50
00:03:34,149 --> 00:03:35,039
Got it?

51
00:03:35,039 --> 00:03:36,129
Yes, I understand.

52
00:03:36,129 --> 00:03:38,139
Now why don't you stop
jumping to conclusions,

53
00:03:38,139 --> 00:03:40,989
relax and really hear
what I have to say.

54
00:03:40,989 --> 00:03:43,029
I know you want to go
after Battosai alone

55
00:03:43,029 --> 00:03:44,149
and I wish you good luck.

56
00:03:44,149 --> 00:03:45,999
So what is this
important information

57
00:03:45,999 --> 00:03:48,069
that you have about him?

58
00:03:48,069 --> 00:03:49,149
He just acquired a new sword

59
00:03:49,149 --> 00:03:51,169
after a fight with our man, Cho.

60
00:03:51,169 --> 00:03:52,169
I already knew that,

61
00:03:52,169 --> 00:03:54,159
so if that's it I'll be going.

62
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:56,159
Stop, I have an idea.

63
00:03:56,159 --> 00:03:57,179
There's an old man named Okina

64
00:03:57,179 --> 00:04:00,899
that would know
Battosai's whereabouts.

65
00:04:00,899 --> 00:04:03,139
Now I know he's a former
member of your Oni Gang, Aoshi,

66
00:04:03,139 --> 00:04:07,929
but if we attack Okina,
Battosai will try to help him.

67
00:04:07,929 --> 00:04:09,099
And if he doesn't
help the old man

68
00:04:09,099 --> 00:04:12,189
we'll torture Okina and
he'll tell where Battosai is.

69
00:04:12,189 --> 00:04:16,099
Hm, that just might work.

70
00:04:16,099 --> 00:04:18,119
What's your feeling
about this plan, Aoshi?

71
00:04:18,119 --> 00:04:19,179
Do you think it would work?

72
00:04:19,179 --> 00:04:23,899
♪

73
00:04:23,899 --> 00:04:25,009
Misao, the time has come

74
00:04:25,009 --> 00:04:27,119
for your Aoshi to move on.

75
00:04:27,119 --> 00:04:32,039
You'll stay here
in my safe care.

76
00:04:32,039 --> 00:04:34,139
Mhmm.

77
00:04:34,139 --> 00:04:36,979
Okina has agreed to
take care of Misao.

78
00:04:36,979 --> 00:04:38,169
At least here she
will have a safer life

79
00:04:38,169 --> 00:04:39,949
than traveling with us.

80
00:04:39,949 --> 00:04:40,959
Right, Han'nya?

81
00:04:40,959 --> 00:04:42,079
I know what you say is true,

82
00:04:42,079 --> 00:04:44,969
but that doesn't change
how much I care about Misao.

83
00:04:44,969 --> 00:04:47,069
I wish she could
stay with our gang.

84
00:04:47,069 --> 00:04:48,189
We all want the best for her

85
00:04:48,189 --> 00:04:51,049
and we agree this
situation's it, right?

86
00:04:51,049 --> 00:04:53,179
This is the best thing
we can do to save her.

87
00:04:53,179 --> 00:04:55,979
Our lives are permeated
with death and danger,

88
00:04:55,979 --> 00:04:58,989
and our precious
Misao deserves better.

89
00:04:58,989 --> 00:05:00,949
Don't lie, Han'nya,
even though you know

90
00:05:00,949 --> 00:05:02,069
this will be good for Misao,

91
00:05:02,069 --> 00:05:03,109
you're hurt inside.

92
00:05:03,109 --> 00:05:06,069
I agree with whatever
you say, boss.

93
00:05:06,069 --> 00:05:07,109
Let's get moving

94
00:05:07,109 --> 00:05:11,999
before I change my
mind about that child.

95
00:05:11,999 --> 00:05:13,139
When I eliminate Battosai

96
00:05:13,139 --> 00:05:15,089
then I can finally
claim the title

97
00:05:15,089 --> 00:05:18,949
of the most powerful
one in all Japan.

98
00:05:18,949 --> 00:05:20,179
So what do you think, Aoshi?

99
00:05:20,179 --> 00:05:23,109
Do you mind if we
move against Okina?

100
00:05:23,109 --> 00:05:27,059
I could care less
what you do to Okina.

101
00:05:27,059 --> 00:05:28,069
The only thing I care about

102
00:05:28,069 --> 00:05:29,159
is having Battosai left alone

103
00:05:29,159 --> 00:05:32,129
for me to deal with.

104
00:05:32,129 --> 00:05:35,899
Then you and I are going
to be working together.

105
00:05:35,899 --> 00:05:36,989
Excuse me, great Shishio,

106
00:05:36,989 --> 00:05:39,069
but there is one
matter that concerns me.

107
00:05:39,069 --> 00:05:39,989
Tell me what it is,

108
00:05:39,989 --> 00:05:41,089
I'm your confessor.

109
00:05:41,089 --> 00:05:43,039
I know Aoshi's a
great swordsman,

110
00:05:43,039 --> 00:05:45,129
but if he can give up a
member of his gang that quickly

111
00:05:45,129 --> 00:05:47,049
how much can we trust him?

112
00:05:47,049 --> 00:05:49,969
About as much as
he can trust us.

113
00:05:49,969 --> 00:05:52,159
Aoshi is a shark that could
turn on us at any moment,

114
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:54,049
but I already knew that.

115
00:05:54,049 --> 00:05:55,939
Of course, I understand.

116
00:05:55,939 --> 00:05:59,079
But for now he serves
a vital purpose for us.

117
00:05:59,079 --> 00:06:02,159
Sojiro, go keep an eye on him.

118
00:06:02,159 --> 00:06:04,179
I'll accompany you.

119
00:06:04,179 --> 00:06:21,059
♪

120
00:06:23,009 --> 00:06:24,989
(shouting)

121
00:06:30,099 --> 00:06:31,179
♪

122
00:06:31,179 --> 00:06:33,029
Just because you
swing your sword

123
00:06:33,029 --> 00:06:35,909
doesn't mean your opponent
will act accordingly.

124
00:06:35,909 --> 00:06:40,999
You're anticipating too many
moves ahead in your mind.

125
00:06:40,999 --> 00:06:43,019
The passage of time has
not been kind to you.

126
00:06:43,019 --> 00:06:44,119
You developed some bad habits

127
00:06:44,119 --> 00:06:46,939
that really need to be broken.

128
00:06:46,939 --> 00:06:48,959
But I don't have much time.

129
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:50,159
Shishio and his
gang are so ruthless

130
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:51,909
that he's probably attacking

131
00:06:51,909 --> 00:06:53,089
even as I sit here practicing.

132
00:06:53,089 --> 00:06:55,089
I must hurry.

133
00:06:55,089 --> 00:06:57,009
Please, teach me a
new move before I go.

134
00:06:57,009 --> 00:07:02,139
♪

135
00:07:02,139 --> 00:07:04,129
I see, he appears to
be sheathing his sword,

136
00:07:04,129 --> 00:07:06,989
but in reality he's doing
the double dragon thrust

137
00:07:06,989 --> 00:07:08,049
sword pulling technique.

138
00:07:08,049 --> 00:07:09,169
It's quite a tricky move.

139
00:07:09,169 --> 00:07:12,979
♪

140
00:07:12,979 --> 00:07:16,019
Ha, I didn't over
anticipate that time.

141
00:07:16,019 --> 00:07:18,049
Now he's gonna remove
his sheathe from his belt

142
00:07:18,049 --> 00:07:19,139
and then he's gonna
pull his sword out

143
00:07:19,139 --> 00:07:21,059
and I can charge in.

144
00:07:21,059 --> 00:07:22,119
Wait a second.

145
00:07:22,119 --> 00:07:25,049
Ahhh!

146
00:07:25,049 --> 00:07:29,969
♪

147
00:07:29,969 --> 00:07:31,939
And to think that you
call yourself a master

148
00:07:31,939 --> 00:07:33,049
of the Hiten Mitsurugi

149
00:07:33,049 --> 00:07:34,109
when you don't even
know how to counter

150
00:07:34,109 --> 00:07:36,099
the double step Ikazuchi.

151
00:07:36,099 --> 00:07:38,939
Hey, get up, stand up straight.

152
00:07:38,939 --> 00:07:40,089
You will never master a new move

153
00:07:40,089 --> 00:07:41,139
if a light hit to the gut

154
00:07:41,139 --> 00:07:43,079
keeps you down
this long, Himura.

155
00:07:43,079 --> 00:07:45,079
Come on, get up.

156
00:07:45,079 --> 00:07:46,929
We haven't got much time.

157
00:07:46,929 --> 00:07:49,909
Besides, I only hit you with
the backside of my sword.

158
00:07:49,909 --> 00:07:51,909
(panting)

159
00:07:51,909 --> 00:07:52,959
Huh?

160
00:07:52,959 --> 00:07:57,119
♪

161
00:07:57,119 --> 00:07:58,189
Look at his eyes.

162
00:07:58,189 --> 00:08:00,009
He still has his fierceness.

163
00:08:00,009 --> 00:08:01,019
He won't quit,

164
00:08:01,019 --> 00:08:02,919
he has the heart of a tiger.

165
00:08:02,919 --> 00:08:04,949
He might not be able
to defeat Shishio,

166
00:08:04,949 --> 00:08:06,009
but if I work him
a little harder

167
00:08:06,009 --> 00:08:08,109
it just might make
the difference.

168
00:08:08,109 --> 00:08:14,939
♪

169
00:08:14,939 --> 00:08:18,039
Sensei, I thank
you for your help.

170
00:08:18,039 --> 00:08:20,149
Now I must go and try
and save my friends.

171
00:08:20,149 --> 00:08:22,909
I don't think you're
quite ready for that.

172
00:08:22,909 --> 00:08:23,959
All right, then.

173
00:08:23,959 --> 00:08:28,019
Let me help you master
that last technique.

174
00:08:28,019 --> 00:08:29,179
And if you don't get
it right this time

175
00:08:29,179 --> 00:08:30,959
you'll be paying
me for this lesson

176
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:32,039
in bruises and lumps.

177
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:34,969
Now let's start again, move.

178
00:08:34,969 --> 00:08:43,909
♪

179
00:08:43,909 --> 00:08:45,069
Fukuro.

180
00:08:45,069 --> 00:08:48,039
The Fukuro are a secret
ninja attack force.

181
00:08:48,039 --> 00:08:50,909
They specialize
in night attacks.

182
00:08:50,909 --> 00:08:53,009
Attacking the hideout of
a former Oni gang member

183
00:08:53,009 --> 00:08:55,119
is like jumping
into a cobra's den.

184
00:08:55,119 --> 00:09:00,969
But I'm sure the Fukuro will
make very short work of Okina.

185
00:09:00,969 --> 00:09:17,049
♪

186
00:09:17,049 --> 00:09:20,009
I'm trying to sleep, you idiots!

187
00:09:20,009 --> 00:09:22,129
All right, I wanna
know just who sent you.

188
00:09:27,949 --> 00:09:31,049
Ha.

189
00:09:31,049 --> 00:09:33,989
In my day our poison
did a lot better job.

190
00:09:36,049 --> 00:09:37,029
Don't yell for your friends,

191
00:09:37,029 --> 00:09:38,149
we already took care of them.

192
00:09:38,149 --> 00:09:40,909
I gave all of them
a knuckle shampoo.

193
00:09:40,909 --> 00:09:42,999
We heard they worked
for Shishio's gang.

194
00:09:42,999 --> 00:09:45,169
This is Aoshi's doing.

195
00:09:45,169 --> 00:09:47,059
Aoshi must have aligned himself

196
00:09:47,059 --> 00:09:49,109
with that bastard, Shishio.

197
00:09:56,999 --> 00:09:58,039
It's six.

198
00:09:58,039 --> 00:10:01,069
I told those Fukuro
to report back here.

199
00:10:01,069 --> 00:10:03,109
Hm?

200
00:10:03,109 --> 00:10:05,019
I got a message for you.

201
00:10:05,019 --> 00:10:07,949
It's...

202
00:10:07,949 --> 00:10:08,969
Damn.

203
00:10:08,969 --> 00:10:10,109
What the hell happened?

204
00:10:10,109 --> 00:10:12,039
My whole Fukuro force
has been wiped out.

205
00:10:12,039 --> 00:10:13,089
I'm not surprised.

206
00:10:13,089 --> 00:10:15,039
You and Shishio's
lackeys have no idea

207
00:10:15,039 --> 00:10:17,959
of how to do a professional job.

208
00:10:17,959 --> 00:10:19,099
So when their
lives depended on it

209
00:10:19,099 --> 00:10:20,159
your killer force
couldn't take out

210
00:10:20,159 --> 00:10:22,169
an old, decrepit
former Oni gangster

211
00:10:22,169 --> 00:10:25,079
even though he
sleeps like a rock.

212
00:10:25,079 --> 00:10:26,139
I suppose I could retrain you,

213
00:10:26,139 --> 00:10:27,169
but it would take years.

214
00:10:30,179 --> 00:10:33,929
"This is a challenge to that
worthless warrior, Aoshi,

215
00:10:33,929 --> 00:10:36,049
who doesn't have the guts
to do his own bidding.

216
00:10:36,049 --> 00:10:38,929
I'll be waiting for you
at the place at high noon.

217
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:40,019
Come alone".

218
00:10:40,019 --> 00:10:42,099
So, Aoshi, just how do
you interpret this message?

219
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:43,989
Will you go?

220
00:10:43,989 --> 00:10:45,159
I understand.

221
00:10:45,159 --> 00:10:48,009
♪

222
00:10:48,009 --> 00:10:49,169
So, Aoshi.

223
00:10:49,169 --> 00:10:51,999
You tarnished the pride
of the Oni Gang once again

224
00:10:51,999 --> 00:10:54,899
with your cowardice
and murdering ways.

225
00:10:54,899 --> 00:10:57,149
You've left me no other
choice but to destroy you.

226
00:10:57,149 --> 00:11:05,979
♪

227
00:11:05,979 --> 00:11:08,969
It's ironic that it
would all come to this.

228
00:11:08,969 --> 00:11:11,019
After the way he helped
me when I needed him

229
00:11:11,019 --> 00:11:15,119
Okina is forcing me to
kill him with my own hands.

230
00:11:15,119 --> 00:11:24,059
♪

231
00:11:24,059 --> 00:11:25,009
Where is he?

232
00:11:25,009 --> 00:11:26,969
I don't know, he left.

233
00:11:26,969 --> 00:11:29,029
So did he tell you
where he was going?

234
00:11:29,029 --> 00:11:31,189
He just put on his
old uniform and left.

235
00:11:31,189 --> 00:11:32,899
Hm.

236
00:11:32,899 --> 00:11:34,009
Hey!

237
00:11:34,009 --> 00:11:37,099
I think he went fishing, Misao.

238
00:11:37,099 --> 00:11:39,009
He looked serious.

239
00:11:39,009 --> 00:11:42,129
If he's wearing his
uniform it's serious.

240
00:11:42,129 --> 00:11:45,919
So I see that he also took
along with him his weapon.

241
00:11:45,919 --> 00:11:48,109
So I guess he's not really
fishing like you said, Kuro.

242
00:11:48,109 --> 00:11:49,189
I'd say he's probably hunting.

243
00:11:49,189 --> 00:11:52,929
Hunting for a fight.

244
00:11:52,929 --> 00:11:54,939
We're sorry, Misao.

245
00:11:54,939 --> 00:11:56,099
He's gone after Aoshi.

246
00:11:56,099 --> 00:11:57,179
Huh?

247
00:11:57,179 --> 00:11:59,009
Did you just say Aoshi?

248
00:11:59,009 --> 00:12:03,069
♪

249
00:12:05,252 --> 00:12:12,152
♪

250
00:12:12,152 --> 00:12:14,182
So you've come Aoshi, well.

251
00:12:14,182 --> 00:12:16,212
I was wondering if on
top of being gutless

252
00:12:16,212 --> 00:12:18,182
that you'd lost your
nerve completely.

253
00:12:18,182 --> 00:12:20,092
You sure lost your honor.

254
00:12:20,092 --> 00:12:21,312
It's about time you
were exterminated

255
00:12:21,312 --> 00:12:25,192
like a filthy rat.

256
00:12:25,192 --> 00:12:28,032
You were a member of the
Oni Gang before I was born.

257
00:12:28,032 --> 00:12:32,062
♪

258
00:12:32,062 --> 00:12:33,272
But now you must die.

259
00:12:33,272 --> 00:12:40,242
♪

260
00:12:40,242 --> 00:12:44,122
Thanks for finally
telling me the truth.

261
00:12:44,122 --> 00:12:45,312
Misao, it's no use,

262
00:12:45,312 --> 00:12:47,252
it's too late to stop them.

263
00:12:47,252 --> 00:12:48,322
I hope the fighting's over

264
00:12:48,322 --> 00:12:50,322
by the time she gets there.

265
00:12:50,322 --> 00:12:52,122
I'm really sorry for her,

266
00:12:52,122 --> 00:12:55,092
she must be feeling
just terrible about this.

267
00:12:55,092 --> 00:12:59,052
She is the loser no
matter who lives or dies.

268
00:12:59,052 --> 00:13:00,062
She's in the middle

269
00:13:00,062 --> 00:13:01,322
between heaven and hell.

270
00:13:01,322 --> 00:13:12,222
♪

271
00:13:12,222 --> 00:13:14,052
If they fight to the death

272
00:13:14,052 --> 00:13:16,142
I'll lose either the man
I'm closest to in my life,

273
00:13:16,142 --> 00:13:20,162
or the one whose
love I want the most.

274
00:13:20,162 --> 00:13:21,282
At this point it's just a matter

275
00:13:21,282 --> 00:13:23,232
of waiting to hear the news.

276
00:13:23,232 --> 00:13:25,262
Well, if you want me
to take care of Okina,

277
00:13:25,262 --> 00:13:27,172
I know Juppongatana well enough

278
00:13:27,172 --> 00:13:29,072
to do the job.

279
00:13:29,072 --> 00:13:31,322
You know that Aoshi is
already on his way, don't you?

280
00:13:31,322 --> 00:13:33,082
Yes, I know.

281
00:13:33,082 --> 00:13:35,042
I've got something
else in mind for you.

282
00:13:35,042 --> 00:13:36,032
What?

283
00:13:36,032 --> 00:13:37,112
Answer this for me, Hoji.

284
00:13:37,112 --> 00:13:39,082
Do you really believe in hell?

285
00:13:39,082 --> 00:13:41,152
No, Shishio, I don't.

286
00:13:41,152 --> 00:13:42,262
Oh, I see.

287
00:13:42,262 --> 00:13:44,112
It doesn't matter
whether you're good or bad.

288
00:13:44,112 --> 00:13:46,172
When we die all we feel is dead.

289
00:13:46,172 --> 00:13:49,062
After we die I don't
think we feel anything.

290
00:13:49,062 --> 00:13:50,112
I disagree.

291
00:13:50,112 --> 00:13:51,272
I believe in hell.

292
00:13:51,272 --> 00:13:54,062
It's real.

293
00:13:54,062 --> 00:13:56,202
Allow me to expound
on my theory.

294
00:13:56,202 --> 00:13:58,162
Let's start with Battosai.

295
00:13:58,162 --> 00:14:00,322
He survived the
bloody Tokugawa era.

296
00:14:00,322 --> 00:14:02,212
He battled Aoshi before.

297
00:14:02,212 --> 00:14:05,132
He knows there's a hell.

298
00:14:05,132 --> 00:14:06,232
How about Okina?

299
00:14:06,232 --> 00:14:08,122
His parents were
killed by Royalists

300
00:14:08,122 --> 00:14:10,122
right before his eyes.

301
00:14:10,122 --> 00:14:11,272
Aoshi has betrayed him.

302
00:14:11,272 --> 00:14:14,042
He knows the pain of hell.

303
00:14:14,042 --> 00:14:15,222
I was burned alive.

304
00:14:15,222 --> 00:14:18,232
Every square inch of my
skin was screaming in pain,

305
00:14:18,232 --> 00:14:20,182
begging to die.

306
00:14:20,182 --> 00:14:23,092
So, Hoji, have I
changed your mind?

307
00:14:23,092 --> 00:14:24,202
Don't you think there's a hell

308
00:14:24,202 --> 00:14:28,312
right here on
earth after all, hm?

309
00:14:28,312 --> 00:14:31,282
Don't you think a world
that's been baptized in blood

310
00:14:31,282 --> 00:14:34,312
should be called hell?

311
00:14:34,312 --> 00:14:37,302
I sense you need
to be persuaded.

312
00:14:37,302 --> 00:14:39,282
And now you shall die!

313
00:14:39,282 --> 00:14:53,162
♪

314
00:14:53,162 --> 00:14:56,282
So it's tonfa.

315
00:14:56,282 --> 00:14:58,292
I think you know deep
in your heart, Aoshi,

316
00:14:58,292 --> 00:15:01,262
that I am the only one that
can beat you one on one.

317
00:15:01,262 --> 00:15:03,112
and I know my steel tonfa

318
00:15:03,112 --> 00:15:06,062
is the answer to your
Kodachi Nitou sword style.

319
00:15:06,062 --> 00:15:07,322
You can't slash
through my defense,

320
00:15:07,322 --> 00:15:09,302
so you had better try
something different.

321
00:15:09,302 --> 00:15:15,142
♪

322
00:15:15,142 --> 00:15:17,212
It's your flowing water attack.

323
00:15:17,212 --> 00:15:20,292
I think this is your
best offensive move.

324
00:15:20,292 --> 00:15:22,072
But you see,

325
00:15:22,072 --> 00:15:23,212
no matter what technique you use

326
00:15:23,212 --> 00:15:26,242
you still have to come
in to get me, right?

327
00:15:26,242 --> 00:15:29,072
And that's when I'll get you.

328
00:15:29,072 --> 00:15:36,272
♪

329
00:15:36,272 --> 00:15:38,062
Crossed Jinyang!

330
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:43,152
♪

331
00:15:43,152 --> 00:15:44,242
My Kodachi Nitou style

332
00:15:44,242 --> 00:15:46,092
sliced through your tonfa

333
00:15:46,092 --> 00:15:49,162
like it was bok choy.

334
00:15:49,162 --> 00:15:50,162
What gave you the illusion

335
00:15:50,162 --> 00:15:53,032
that you could defeat me, Okina?

336
00:15:53,032 --> 00:15:54,202
I don't care that you
were in the Oni Gang

337
00:15:54,202 --> 00:15:55,282
or about your tonfa,

338
00:15:55,282 --> 00:15:58,092
there's nothing my
twin swords can't stop.

339
00:15:58,092 --> 00:16:01,122
♪

340
00:16:01,122 --> 00:16:02,262
Please don't let
them kill each other.

341
00:16:02,262 --> 00:16:05,102
Okina, Aoshi, be alive.

342
00:16:05,102 --> 00:16:08,262
♪

343
00:16:08,262 --> 00:16:10,112
He's so skillful.

344
00:16:10,112 --> 00:16:13,132
There's no comparison to
the Aoshi I knew years ago.

345
00:16:13,132 --> 00:16:14,232
He's even better now than he was

346
00:16:14,232 --> 00:16:16,252
as head of the Oni Gang.

347
00:16:16,252 --> 00:16:18,072
By forsaking his emotions

348
00:16:18,072 --> 00:16:19,192
and turning into a murderer

349
00:16:19,192 --> 00:16:21,242
he's truly tapped
his inner strength.

350
00:16:21,242 --> 00:16:25,082
He's found a twisted
path to enlightenment.

351
00:16:25,082 --> 00:16:26,062
I'll give you one more chance

352
00:16:26,062 --> 00:16:27,272
to tell me about Battosai.

353
00:16:27,272 --> 00:16:29,112
Where is he?

354
00:16:29,112 --> 00:16:30,152
Tell me where he is, Okina,

355
00:16:30,152 --> 00:16:32,122
and I won't attack you again.

356
00:16:32,122 --> 00:16:34,242
You insult my courage?

357
00:16:34,242 --> 00:16:35,322
I'm just an old solider,

358
00:16:35,322 --> 00:16:37,112
but I'm not like you.

359
00:16:37,112 --> 00:16:38,312
I will not change my principles

360
00:16:38,312 --> 00:16:40,292
to satisfy your needs.

361
00:16:40,292 --> 00:16:42,032
I'll never give in!

362
00:16:42,032 --> 00:16:47,042
♪

363
00:16:47,042 --> 00:16:48,132
I see.

364
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:49,282
You leave me no other
choice, old friend,

365
00:16:49,282 --> 00:16:51,042
but to kill you and go to town

366
00:16:51,042 --> 00:16:53,242
to ask the others.

367
00:16:53,242 --> 00:16:54,252
You know with those words

368
00:16:54,252 --> 00:16:56,172
you've chosen to die.

369
00:16:56,172 --> 00:17:00,192
♪

370
00:17:00,192 --> 00:17:02,082
I'll give up my
life to defeat you.

371
00:17:02,082 --> 00:17:04,032
I must give my all
to protect Himura

372
00:17:04,032 --> 00:17:07,162
and defend our country from
people like you and Shishio.

373
00:17:07,162 --> 00:17:16,062
♪

374
00:17:16,062 --> 00:17:19,192
No.

375
00:17:19,192 --> 00:17:20,272
Ah!

376
00:17:20,272 --> 00:17:22,292
Please Buddha, don't
let me be too late.

377
00:17:22,292 --> 00:17:30,252
♪

378
00:17:30,252 --> 00:17:32,242
Oh!

379
00:17:32,242 --> 00:17:35,222
♪

380
00:17:35,222 --> 00:17:37,072
Got ya.

381
00:17:37,072 --> 00:17:39,132
Huh?

382
00:17:39,132 --> 00:17:40,282
That stance he's in.

383
00:17:40,282 --> 00:17:43,102
Dammit, it's the
Herculean Sword Dance.

384
00:17:55,102 --> 00:17:57,082
You're both all right.

385
00:17:57,082 --> 00:18:06,042
♪

386
00:18:06,042 --> 00:18:09,052
Okina's life's over.

387
00:18:09,052 --> 00:18:20,202
♪

388
00:18:20,202 --> 00:18:25,042
Wait, Mr. Aoshi.

389
00:18:25,042 --> 00:18:29,202
How, how could you?

390
00:18:29,202 --> 00:18:34,192
Why did you do it?

391
00:18:34,192 --> 00:18:36,072
Go away, Misao.

392
00:18:36,072 --> 00:18:37,192
If you're not really on my side

393
00:18:37,192 --> 00:18:41,252
I never wanna see you again.

394
00:18:41,252 --> 00:18:43,112
Do me a favor and tell Battosai

395
00:18:43,112 --> 00:18:44,112
I'll be waiting for him

396
00:18:44,112 --> 00:18:46,252
at Shishio's hideout.

397
00:18:51,322 --> 00:18:53,172
I see.

398
00:18:53,172 --> 00:18:56,112
But what is it that makes
your hand as hot as fire?

399
00:18:56,112 --> 00:18:57,252
When they tried to
burn me to death

400
00:18:57,252 --> 00:19:00,152
one of the results was
that my body's sweat glands

401
00:19:00,152 --> 00:19:02,162
were completely destroyed.

402
00:19:02,162 --> 00:19:05,162
Since then my body gives
off intense amounts of heat

403
00:19:05,162 --> 00:19:08,202
through my hands and
other parts of my body.

404
00:19:08,202 --> 00:19:11,132
Sometimes it's so hot
I feel like I'm on fire.

405
00:19:11,132 --> 00:19:14,312
♪

406
00:19:14,312 --> 00:19:17,082
This heat has changed
the way my brain works,

407
00:19:17,082 --> 00:19:20,212
it's given me new insights into
our world and our experiences.

408
00:19:20,212 --> 00:19:23,112
I've accessed a deeper truth.

409
00:19:23,112 --> 00:19:26,132
Through this phenomena I've
made some startling discoveries.

410
00:19:26,132 --> 00:19:29,122
The true nature of
man is to murder.

411
00:19:29,122 --> 00:19:31,042
This world is a living hell

412
00:19:31,042 --> 00:19:35,052
and my goal is to
fill it with murderers.

413
00:19:35,052 --> 00:19:37,322
And I will be the leader
of this murderous nation.

414
00:19:37,322 --> 00:19:39,102
If you don't believe in hell

415
00:19:39,102 --> 00:19:43,262
then why the hell should
I keep you around, Hoji?

416
00:19:43,262 --> 00:19:45,292
Why are you visibly shaking?

417
00:19:45,292 --> 00:19:47,232
I hope I haven't scared you.

418
00:19:47,232 --> 00:19:48,212
No, Sir, I,

419
00:19:48,212 --> 00:19:51,092
I am just trembling with joy.

420
00:19:51,092 --> 00:19:52,222
It's rare that a
man is lucky enough

421
00:19:52,222 --> 00:19:54,152
to serve a leader of destiny.

422
00:19:54,152 --> 00:19:57,262
Someone brave enough
to build a new Japan.

423
00:19:57,262 --> 00:19:59,112
I was shaking
because I'm so excited

424
00:19:59,112 --> 00:20:00,232
just standing here with you.

425
00:20:00,232 --> 00:20:02,032
It's great, Ayumi,

426
00:20:02,032 --> 00:20:03,322
to see the conversion of
yet another loyal murderer

427
00:20:03,322 --> 00:20:07,052
to our vision.

428
00:20:08,092 --> 00:20:10,132
He had 35 stab wounds.

429
00:20:10,132 --> 00:20:11,312
Even though Okina survived,

430
00:20:11,312 --> 00:20:14,322
the doctor said he
could die any time.

431
00:20:14,322 --> 00:20:15,312
That's for sure.

432
00:20:15,312 --> 00:20:16,322
He was lucky.

433
00:20:16,322 --> 00:20:18,102
I guess it's kind of a miracle

434
00:20:18,102 --> 00:20:20,172
he lived through it all.

435
00:20:20,172 --> 00:20:22,152
But he's still not
out of the woods yet.

436
00:20:22,152 --> 00:20:24,312
Okina lost a lot of blood.

437
00:20:24,312 --> 00:20:26,322
So how's Misao taking this?

438
00:20:26,322 --> 00:20:28,212
She's fine.

439
00:20:28,212 --> 00:20:31,172
She seems to be holding
it together for a girl.

440
00:20:31,172 --> 00:20:32,182
Don't call her that!

441
00:20:32,182 --> 00:20:33,122
Shut up!

442
00:20:33,122 --> 00:20:34,172
You sure got a lot of nerve.

443
00:20:34,172 --> 00:20:35,282
So who died and made you Buddha?

444
00:20:35,282 --> 00:20:37,082
You sure have a big mouth

445
00:20:37,082 --> 00:20:40,212
for someone with
such a wimpy body.

446
00:20:40,212 --> 00:20:42,092
(shouting)

447
00:20:42,092 --> 00:20:45,172
♪

448
00:20:45,172 --> 00:20:46,242
Misao.

449
00:20:46,242 --> 00:20:49,182
There's something I need
to share with you now.

450
00:20:49,182 --> 00:20:53,202
Okina told me to give this to
you if anything bad happened.

451
00:20:53,202 --> 00:20:55,132
"For Misao.

452
00:20:59,172 --> 00:21:02,212
Ciao, my lovely Misao".

453
00:21:02,212 --> 00:21:07,142
Oh.

454
00:21:07,142 --> 00:21:09,182
Ciao, my lovely Misao.

455
00:21:09,182 --> 00:21:12,112
The fact that you're reading
this means that I've passed on,

456
00:21:12,112 --> 00:21:13,222
but don't shed tears,

457
00:21:13,222 --> 00:21:15,152
don't be sad.

458
00:21:15,152 --> 00:21:17,252
You can still find me
in the summer wind,

459
00:21:17,252 --> 00:21:20,212
you can feel my warmth
in the morning sun.

460
00:21:20,212 --> 00:21:22,212
I will always be with you.

461
00:21:22,212 --> 00:21:26,062
When I decided to fight Aoshi
I knew it would be dangerous.

462
00:21:26,062 --> 00:21:28,122
I'm ready to die the
death of a warrior.

463
00:21:28,122 --> 00:21:31,122
As of now the Oni
Gang no longer exists.

464
00:21:31,122 --> 00:21:34,172
Leave any fighting
or revenge to Kenshin.

465
00:21:34,172 --> 00:21:36,092
Now, my dear, please listen.

466
00:21:36,092 --> 00:21:38,212
You must give up your
dangerous lifestyle.

467
00:21:38,212 --> 00:21:40,032
Learn to exist peacefully

468
00:21:40,032 --> 00:21:43,152
and live a normal life.

469
00:21:43,152 --> 00:21:46,062
How can I do what you ask of me?

470
00:21:46,062 --> 00:21:50,052
♪

471
00:21:50,052 --> 00:21:52,052
Misao, what is it?

472
00:21:52,052 --> 00:21:54,042
The Oni Gang still lives.

473
00:21:54,042 --> 00:21:55,242
And I will not let it die.

474
00:21:55,242 --> 00:21:56,302
No, Sir.

475
00:21:56,302 --> 00:21:58,252
Aoshi is through as
the gang's leader,

476
00:21:58,252 --> 00:22:02,272
and I will be the new
leader of the Oni Gang.

477
00:22:02,272 --> 00:22:04,212
I will stop Shishio
and his followers

478
00:22:04,212 --> 00:22:06,292
by working with Himura
to see them crushed.

479
00:22:06,292 --> 00:22:09,062
I'm planning a special
kind of revenge for Aoshi.

480
00:22:09,062 --> 00:22:12,042
When I get my hands on that
spineless eel he'll be dead.

481
00:22:12,042 --> 00:22:13,222
Oh, yeah.

482
00:22:13,222 --> 00:22:18,152
♪

483
00:22:18,152 --> 00:22:20,212
Okina, how could you
ask me to turn my back

484
00:22:20,212 --> 00:22:23,292
on the only family
I've ever known?

485
00:22:23,292 --> 00:22:25,102
I will rebuild the Oni Gang.

486
00:22:25,102 --> 00:22:27,162
Once again its members will
possess the code of honor

487
00:22:27,162 --> 00:22:28,252
exemplified by Okina,

488
00:22:28,252 --> 00:22:30,132
a man of courage and respect.

489
00:22:30,132 --> 00:22:33,242
There is no happiness
for me without this.

490
00:22:33,242 --> 00:22:35,252
Misao, I hope you'll
take this the right way,

491
00:22:35,252 --> 00:22:37,192
but were you struck in the head

492
00:22:37,192 --> 00:22:39,082
while you were sparring today?

493
00:22:39,082 --> 00:22:41,042
I'm not Misao anymore.

494
00:22:41,042 --> 00:22:43,042
From now on call me boss.

495
00:22:43,042 --> 00:22:45,252
I'm the boss of the Oni Gang.

496
00:22:47,192 --> 00:22:51,312
♪

497
00:22:51,312 --> 00:22:54,202
♪ (singing in Japanese) ♪

498
00:22:54,202 --> 00:25:09,082
♪

